value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of cytochrome-c oxidase activity is decreased.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'decreased cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000342).

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquinol-cytochrome-c reductase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquinol-cytochrome-c reductase activity is decreased.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of cerulenin than normal.
A cell population phenotype in which a population in a culture remains in lag phase longer than normal. The onset of exponential growth is thus delayed.

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of microtubule binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is abnormal. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with microtubules that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which microtubule binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with microtubules that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein secretion is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid separation does not occur.

label.value: increased level of substance in cytosol

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a specific substance measured in the cytosol is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of calcium ion measured in the cytosol is higher than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of calcium ion determined to be sequestered in a cell is lower than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of calcium ions out of a cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of calcium ions out of a cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of calcium ions into a cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of calcium ions into a cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is shaped in the form of a spheroid. In spheroid cells, there is much less difference between the long and short axes of the cell than in wild type. Spheroid cells may shorter than normal, with approximately the same diameter as normal, or they may be enlarged.
A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is formed in the shape of a sphere.

label.value: normal cAMP level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of cyclic AMP measured in a cell during nitrogen starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA topoisomerase II activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of DNA topoisomerase II activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which a protein phosphatase activity is absent.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of papulacandin B than normal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of aculeacin A than normal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of papulacandin D than normal.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to aculeacin A. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of aculeacin A that allows wild type cells to grow.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity is increased.

label.value: increased 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity during growth on papulacandin B

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity is increased when cells are grown in medium containing papulacandin B.

label.value: increased 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity during growth on aculeacin A

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity is increased when cells are grown in medium containing aculeacin A.

label.value: abnormal cell separation after cytokinesis resulting in chained cells

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation after cytokinesis is abnormal, and results in the formation of a chain of cells. Cells in the chain visually resemble wild-type cells, except that they remain connected, often via remnants of septum edging material, and may continue to undergo normal mitosis and septum formation.

definition.value: This phenotype usually results from a defect late in septum degradation.

label.value: abnormal cell separation after cytokinesis resulting in septated cell

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation after cytokinesis is abnormal, and results in the formation of a septated cell. Nuclear division, contractile ring formation and constriction, and septum assembly are apparently normal, but the septum does not degrade. Additional rounds of nuclear division and cytokinesis may take place, resulting in the formation of a multiseptate cell.

definition.value: This phenotype usually results from a defect late in septum degradation.

label.value: increased number of cells with 1C DNA content

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a greater than normal number of cells contain 1C DNA content. This may result from cell cycle arrest or delay.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing nocodazole.

label.value: normal cytoplasmic microtubules during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount, distribution, and morphology of cytoplasmic microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of galactomannan measured in the cell wall is greater than normal.
A spindle phenotype in which the mitotic spindle is not straight, but instead forms an angle where microtubules from opposite poles interdigitate.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which excised introns in lariat form (i.e. not linearized) are present at greater levels than normal.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNA processing is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). RNA processing is the conversion of one or more primary RNA transcripts into one or more mature RNA molecules.
A cellular process phenotype in which the rate, or speed, of DNA replication is decreased.

label.value: decreased rate of DNA replication during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of DNA replication is decreased.
A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is too low to detect. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: protein absent from cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is too low to detect. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A phenotype that shows detectable differences from normal. In fission yeast, the characteristics of wild type cells of the sequenced strain (972 h-) or the isogenic h+ or h90 strains are regarded as normal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of 5-fluorouracil than normal.

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to pH higher than that of standard S. pombe growth media (about 5.8). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a pH that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal cell population growth at high pH

value.value: A cell population growth phenotype in which vegetative cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) at a pH higher than that of standard S. pombe growth medium (abut 5.8).

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to pH lower than that of standard S. pombe growth media (about 5.8). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a pH that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal cell population growth at low pH

value.value: A cell population growth phenotype in which vegetative cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) at a pH lower than that of standard S. pombe growth medium (abut 5.8).

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that dies without completing cell division.
